  "response": "Yes, it\u2019s possible to have an hourglass body shape and have small breasts and/or a smaller butt. The hourglass body shape is primarily defined by the proportions of your waist in relation to your bust and hips, rather than the size of those areas. Here\u2019s how it works:\n\n- **Hourglass Shape Characteristics**: Your bust and hip measurements are roughly the same, with a significantly narrower waist. This creates a balanced, curvy silhouette.\n- **Small Breasts/Butt**: Even if your bust and butt are on the smaller side, as long as your waist is noticeably smaller in proportion to your bust and hips, you can still have an hourglass shape.\n\nFor example:\n- Someone with a 32-inch bust, 26-inch waist, and 32-inch hips would have an hourglass shape, even if their breasts and butt are small.\n- The emphasis is on the ratio, not the size.\n\nClothing choices, posture, and muscle tone can also enhance or emphasize your natural proportions. Ultimately, body shape labels are just one way to describe your unique figure, and everyone\u2019s body is different!",
